危機爆發前的幾年，資產價格過高上漲，經濟需求相應增長。<ref>{{Cite news |url = https://www.theguardian.com/business/2008/jun/03/commodities |title = Oil prices: George Soros warns that speculators could trigger stock market crash |last = Wearden |first = Graeme |date = 2008-06-03 |publisher = The Guardian |accessdate = 2009-04-10 |location = London |archive-date = 2019-12-27 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191227203756/https://www.theguardian.com/business/2008/jun/03/commodities |dead-url = no }}</ref>此外，美國的[[影子銀行|影子銀行]]系統（例如投資銀行等非儲蓄金融機構）已經成長至可與儲蓄系統相匹敵，但卻不受相同的監管監督，使其容易受到[[擠提|擠提]]的衝擊。<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/24/business/economy/24panel.html| title=Greenspan Concedes Error on Regulation| last=Andrews| first=Edmund L.| work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]| date=2008-10-24| accessdate=2019-11-11| archive-date=2018-04-06| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180406173958/https://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/24/business/economy/24panel.html| dead-url=no}}</ref>

美國抵押擔保[[證券|證券]]雖然有難以估價的風險，但在全球範圍內暢銷，因為它們提供的收益率高於美國政府債券。其中許多證券由[[次级贷款|次級抵押貸款]]支持，而次貸抵押貸款在2006年美國房地產泡沫破裂時崩盤，大量房主從2007年開始違約。<ref>{{Cite news |url = https://www.forbes.com/2009/01/14/global-recession-2009-oped-cx_nr_0115roubini.html |title = A Global Breakdown Of The Recession In 2009 |author = [[Nouriel_Roubini|Nouriel Roubini]] |date = 2009-01-15 |work = Forbes |accessdate = 2019-11-11 |archive-date = 2011-01-27 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110127194730/http://www.forbes.com/2009/01/14/global-recession-2009-oped-cx_nr_0115roubini.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>

2007年次級貸款虧損問題的浮現標誌着危機開始，並暴露了其他有風險貸款和資產價格泡沫的情況。隨著貸款虧損的增加和[[雷曼兄弟|雷曼兄弟]]在2008年9月15日破產，同業拆借市場爆發了重大恐慌。影子銀行系統上出現了類似擠兌的現象，導致歐美許多大型且信譽良好的投資銀行和商業銀行遭受巨大損失，甚至面臨破產，需要大規模的公共財政援助（政府救市）。<ref name="KrugmanGeithner1">{{cite web |url = http://www.nybooks.com/articles/archives/2014/jul/10/geithner-does-he-pass-test/ |title = NYT-Paul Krugman-Geithner: Does He Pass The Test? |publisher = Nybooks.com |date = 2014-07-10 |accessdate = 2014-08-23 |archive-date = 2015-11-05 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151105050812/http://www.nybooks.com/articles/archives/2014/jul/10/geithner-does-he-pass-test/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>

隨後的全球經濟衰退導致[[國際貿易|國際貿易]]量急劇下降、失業率上升和商品價格暴跌。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://money.cnn.com/2008/12/01/news/economy/recession/index.htm?postversion=2008120112|title=It's official: Recession since Dec '07|last=Isidore|first=Chris|date=2008-12-01|publisher=CNN Money|accessdate=2009-04-10|archive-date=2010-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101112154355/http://money.cnn.com/2008/12/01/news/economy/recession/index.htm?postversion=2008120112|dead-url=no}}</ref>一些經濟學家預測，復甦可能要到2011年才會出現，本次衰退將是自1930年代[[大蕭條|大蕭條]]以來最嚴重的一次。<ref>[http://www.mcclatchydc.com/251/story/60822.html Congressional Budget Office compares downturn to Great Depression] {{Wayback|url=http://www.mcclatchydc.com/251/story/60822.html |date=20090303075017 }}. By David Lightman. ''McClatchy Washington Bureau.'' January 27, 2009.</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url = https://www.theguardian.com/business/2009/jan/26/road-ruin-recession-individuals-economy |title = Twenty-five People at the Heart of the Meltdown |last = Finch |first = Julia |date = 2009-01-26 |publisher = The Guardian |accessdate = 2009-04-10 |location = London |archive-date = 2019-11-01 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191101000733/https://www.theguardian.com/business/2009/jan/26/road-ruin-recession-individuals-economy |dead-url = no }}</ref>經濟學家[[保罗·克鲁格曼|保罗·克鲁格曼]]（Paul Krugman）曾經評論說，這似乎是「第二次大蕭條」的開始。<ref>{{Cite news |url = https://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/05/opinion/05krugman.html |last = Krugman |first = Paul |date = 2009-01-04 |title = Fighting Off Depression |publisher = The New York Times. |accessdate = 2019-11-11 |archive-date = 2011-04-30 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110430040012/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/05/opinion/05krugman.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>

各國政府和中央銀行以[[財政政策|財政政策]]和[[貨幣政策|貨幣政策]]舉措回應，以刺激國民經濟並降低金融系統風險。衰退重新引起了人們對[[凯恩斯主义经济学|凱恩斯主義]]關於如何應對衰退狀況的經濟思想的興趣。經濟學家建議，一旦經濟復甦到足以「描繪可持續增長之路」，就應停止刺激計劃。<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.imf.org/external/pubs/ft/weo/2009/01/pdf/c1.pdf |title = IMF World Economic Outlook, April 2009: "Exit strategies will be needed to transition fiscal and monetary policies from extraordinary short-term support to sustainable medium-term frameworks." (p.38) |date =   |accessdate = 2010-01-21 |archive-date = 2009-05-20 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090520150012/http://www.imf.org/external/pubs/ft/weo/2009/01/pdf/c1.pdf |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url = https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=aMK3Z_HHbYM8 |title = Olivier Blanchard, the chief economist of the International Monetary Fund, "is advising officials around the world to keep economic stimulus programs in place no longer than necessary to chart a path to sustainable growth." |publisher = Bloomberg.com |date = 2005-05-30 |accessdate = 2010-01-21 |archive-date = 2015-10-01 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151001190325/http://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=aMK3Z_HHbYM8 |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url = https://www.reuters.com/article/newsOne/idUKTRE57K5IV20090821?virtualBrandChannel=11611 |title = U.S deficit poses potential systemic risk: Taylor |publisher = Reuters.com |date = 2009-08-21 |accessdate = 2010-01-21 |first = Kristin |last = Cooke |archive-date = 2009-08-28 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090828095200/http://www.reuters.com/article/newsOne/idUKTRE57K5IV20090821?virtualBrandChannel=11611 |dead-url = no }}</ref>

在2008年後的[[經濟復甦|經濟復甦]]期間，美國家庭收入分配變得更加不平等。<ref name=Appelbaum>{{cite news |last1 = Binyamin |first1 = Appelbaum |title = Fed Says Growth Lifts the Affluent, Leaving Behind Everyone Else |url = https://www.nytimes.com/2014/09/05/business/economy/least-affluent-families-incomes-are-declining-fed-survey-shows.html |accessdate = 2014-09-13 |work = New York Times |date = 2014-09-04 |archive-date = 2019-08-18 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190818072401/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/09/05/business/economy/least-affluent-families-incomes-are-declining-fed-survey-shows.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>從2005年到2012年，美國超過三分之二的[[大都市區|大都市區]]的收入不平等現像有所加劇。<ref name=Chokshi>{{cite news |last1 = Chokshi |first1 = Niraj |title = Income inequality seems to be rising in more than 2 in 3 metro areas |url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/govbeat/wp/2014/08/11/income-inequality-seems-to-be-rising-in-more-than-2-in-3-metro-areas/ |accessdate = 2014-09-13 |work = Washington Post |date = 2014-08-11 |archive-date = 2019-12-28 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191228041354/https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/govbeat/wp/2014/08/11/income-inequality-seems-to-be-rising-in-more-than-2-in-3-metro-areas/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>2005年至2011年之間，美國家庭財富中位數下降了35%，從106,591美元降至68,839美元。<ref name=Kurtzleben>{{cite news |last1 = Kurtzleben |first1 = Danielle |title = Middle class households' wealth fell 35 percent from 2005 to 2011 |url = https://www.vox.com/2014/8/23/6057467/middle-class-households-wealth-fell-35-percent-from-2005-to-2011 |accessdate = 2014-09-13 |work = Vox.com |date = 2014-08-23 |archive-date = 2019-12-27 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191227204105/https://www.vox.com/2014/8/23/6057467/middle-class-households-wealth-fell-35-percent-from-2005-to-2011 |dead-url = no }}</ref>

