2011年1月，6名民主黨人和4名共和黨人組成的美國{{tsl|en|Financial Crisis Inquiry Commission|金融危機調查委員會}}提供的多數報告公佈了調查結果。報告得出結論：「這場危機是可以避免的，其起因是：

* 金融監管的普遍失靈，包括[[联邦储备系统|联邦储备系统]]未能阻止有毒抵押貸款的趨勢；
* 公司治理方面的嚴重失誤，包括太多金融公司鲁莽行事，承擔過高風險；
* 過度借貸、家庭風險和華爾街的風險爆炸物混合，將金融體系拖入通往危機的軌道；
* 關鍵決策者對危機準備不足，對他們所監管的金融體系缺乏全面認識；各個層級都系統性地違背了責任制和道德規範。」<ref name="stanford1">{{cite web |url = http://fcic.law.stanford.edu/report/conclusions |title = Financial Crisis Inquiry Report-Conclusions-January 2011 |publisher = Fcic.law.stanford.edu |date = 2011-03-10 |accessdate = 2013-04-22 |archive-date = 2019-09-06 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190906204608/http://fcic.law.stanford.edu/report/conclusions |dead-url = no }}</ref>

共和黨有兩份反對委員會結論的報告。其中一個由三名共和黨任命的人簽署，得出結論認為原因多種多樣。[[美國企業研究所|美國企業研究所]]（AEI）的委員{{Tsl|en|Peter J. Wallison|彼得·J·沃里森}}在他另一份對調查委員會的異議中認為，此次危機主要歸咎於美國的住房政策，包括[[房利美|房利美]]和[[房地美|房地美]]的行動。他寫道：「當泡沫在2007年中開始消失時，政府政策產生的低質量和高風險貸款以前所未有的數量破產了。」<ref>{{cite web |url = http://fcic-static.law.stanford.edu/cdn_media/fcic-reports/fcic_final_report_wallison_dissent.pdf |title = FCIC-Final Report Dissent of Wallison |date = January 2011 |accessdate = 2019-11-11 |archive-date = 2016-01-19 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160119194711/http://fcic-static.law.stanford.edu/cdn_media/fcic-reports/fcic_final_report_wallison_dissent.pdf |dead-url = no }}</ref>

[[二十國集團|二十國集團]]領導人在2008年11月15日發表的《金融市場與世界經濟峰會宣言》中列舉了以下原因：

{{quote|近年来，全球经济增势强劲，并长期保持稳定，资本流动加快，市场参与者追逐更高收益，却未恰当评估风险和应履行的责任。与此同时，宽松的承销标准，风险管理措施不到位，日益复杂和不透明的金融产品，以及随之产生的过度杠杆操作，共同造成金融体系的脆弱性。在一些发达国家，决策者、监管者和监督者未能充分评估并解决金融市场不断累积的风险，未能跟上金融创新步伐，未能考虑国内监管行动带来的系统性后果。<ref>{{cite web |url = https://georgewbush-whitehouse.archives.gov/news/releases/2008/11/20081115-1.html |title = Declaration of G20 |publisher = Whitehouse.gov |date = November 2008 |access-date = 2019-11-11 |archive-date = 2009-07-15 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090715083739/http://georgewbush-whitehouse.archives.gov/news/releases/2008/11/20081115-1.html |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://world.people.com.cn/n1/2016/0816/c1002-28640497.html|title=资料：二十国集团领导人金融市场和世界经济华盛顿峰会宣言|via=人民网-国际频道|date=2016-08-16|access-date=2019-11-11|archive-date=2020-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200825025330/http://world.people.com.cn/n1/2016/0816/c1002-28640497.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>}}

=== 敘事 ===
[[File:U.S._Fixed_Investment_as_Pct_GDP.png|thumb]]
有一些「敘事」試圖將經濟衰退的原因放在大背景中。其中五種如下：

# [[影子銀行|影子銀行]]系統上出現了類似[[擠兌|擠兌]]的現象，影子銀行包括投資銀行和其他非存款金融實體。該系統在規模上已經可以與儲蓄系統相媲美，但並未受到相同的監管保障。它的失靈破壞了向消費者和公司的信貸流。<ref name="KrugmanGeithner1"/><ref name="frbatlanta.org">{{cite web |url = http://www.frbatlanta.org/news/CONFEREN/09fmc/gorton.pdf |title = Gary Gorton-NBER and Yale-Slapped in the Face by the Invisible Hand: Banking and the Panic of 2007 |date = May 2009 |accessdate = 2019-11-12 |archive-date = 2014-06-20 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140620164026/http://www.frbatlanta.org/news/CONFEREN/09fmc/gorton.pdf |dead-url = no }}</ref>
# 美國經濟受到房地產泡沫的推動。當泡沫破裂時，私人住宅投資（即住房建設）下降了GDP的4％以上。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://fred.stlouisfed.org/graph/?graph_id=545431 |title=FRED-Private Residential Investment-Retrieved March 3, 2019 |accessdate=2019-11-12 |archive-date=2020-02-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223035836/https://fred.stlouisfed.org/graph/?graph_id=545431 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://research.stlouisfed.org/publications/economic-synopses/2016/01/08/private-investment-and-the-great-recession/|title=Private Investment and the Great Recession|first=Fernando M.|last=Martin|website=research.stlouisfed.org|accessdate=2019-11-12|archive-date=2019-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191016224452/https://research.stlouisfed.org/publications/economic-synopses/2016/01/08/private-investment-and-the-great-recession/|dead-url=no}}</ref>由泡沫產生的住房財富推動的消費也放緩了。這導致年需求（GDP）缺口接近1萬億美元。美國政府不願彌補這一私營部門的缺口。<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.cepr.net/index.php/blogs/beat-the-press/robert-samuelson-wants-people-to-be-unemployed-the-economics-of-the-economics-of-the-great-recession |title = CEPR-Dean Baker-The Economics of the Great Recession-June 29, 2014 |publisher = Cepr.net |date = 2014-06-29 |accessdate = 2014-08-23 |archive-date = 2015-04-02 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150402094309/http://www.cepr.net/index.php/blogs/beat-the-press/robert-samuelson-wants-people-to-be-unemployed-the-economics-of-the-economics-of-the-great-recession |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://krugman.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/07/01/learned-macroeconomic-helplessness/?module=BlogPost-Title&version=Blog+Main&contentCollection=Opinion&action=Click&pgtype=Blogs&region=Body|title=Learned Macroeconomic Helplessness|publisher=|accessdate=2018-03-14|archive-date=2020-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223035849/https://krugman.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/07/01/learned-macroeconomic-helplessness/?module=BlogPost-Title&version=Blog+Main&contentCollection=Opinion&action=Click&pgtype=Blogs&region=Body|dead-url=no}}</ref>
# 在2006年住房價格開始下跌之後，危機爆發前幾十年的{{Tsl|en|household debt|家庭債務}}積累達到創紀錄水平，導致[[資產負債表衰退|資產負債表衰退]]（類似於[[債務通縮|債務通縮]]）。消費者開始還清債務，這減少了他們的消費，使經濟長期放緩、債務水平降低。<ref name="KrugmanGeithner1"/><ref name="Mian and Sufi2014">{{cite book |last = Mian, Atif and |first = Sufi, Amir |year = 2014 |title = House of Debt |publisher = University of Chicago |isbn = 978-0-226-08194-6 |title-link = House of Debt }}</ref>
# 美國政府的政策鼓勵那些無力負擔的人擁有房屋，導致寬鬆的放貸標準、不可持續的住房價格上漲和負債。<ref name="Sowell 2009">{{cite book|title=The Housing Boom and Bust|last=Sowell|first=Thomas|publisher=Basic Books|year=2009|isbn=978-0-465-01880-2|pages=[https://archive.org/details/housingboombust0000sowe/page/57 57]–58|authorlink=Thomas Sowell|title-link=The Housing Boom and Bust}}</ref>
# 信用評分優良的富裕和中產階級[[炒賣|炒房]]客造成了房價的[[泡沫经济|投機泡沫]]，然後在大規模拖欠債務後破壞了當地的房地產市場和金融機構。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://qz.com/1064061/house-flippers-triggered-the-us-housing-market-crash-not-poor-subprime-borrowers-a-new-study-shows/|title=House flippers triggered the US housing market crash, not poor subprime borrowers|first=Gwynn|last=Guilford|publisher=|accessdate=2018-03-14|archive-date=2019-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191027064540/https://qz.com/1064061/house-flippers-triggered-the-us-housing-market-crash-not-poor-subprime-borrowers-a-new-study-shows/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

1-3的基本假設是，收入不平等和工資停滯不斷加劇，促使家庭增加債務以維持他們期望的生活水平，從而加劇了泡沫。此外，更多的收入流向最高階層，增強了商業利益的政治力量，而這種力量被用來放鬆或減少對影子銀行系統的監管。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.american.edu/cas/economics/pdf/upload/2012-1.pdf|title=Jon Wisman-Wage Stagnation, Rising Inequality and the Crisis of 2008-Retrieved June 2015|publisher=|accessdate=2018-03-14|archive-date=2017-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808053920/http://www.american.edu/cas/economics/pdf/upload/2012-1.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imf.org/external/pubs/ft/wp/2010/wp10268.pdf|title=IMF-Inequality, Leverage and Crises-Kumhoff and Ranciere-November 2010|publisher=|accessdate=2018-03-14|archive-date=2019-09-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190911223321/https://www.imf.org/external/pubs/ft/wp/2010/wp10268.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.peri.umass.edu/fileadmin/pdf/working_papers/working_papers_251-300/WP282.pdf|title=Stockhammer-Rising Inequality as a Cause of the Present Crisis-Amherst PERI-April 2012|publisher=|accessdate=2018-03-14|archive-date=2020-02-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228143411/http://www.peri.umass.edu/fileadmin/pdf/working_papers/working_papers_251-300/WP282.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

5挑戰了「信譽欠佳的次級借款人購置無力負擔的房屋造成了危機」這一普遍說法。這種敘事得到了新研究的支持，研究表明，在美國住房市場繁榮期間，抵押貸款債務的最大增長來自信用評分中處於中部和頂部的信用評分良好的人，而這些借款人佔違約比例很高。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mitsloan.mit.edu/newsroom/articles/rethinking-how-the-housing-crisis-happened/|title=Rethinking how the housing crisis happened|website=mitsloan.mit.edu|accessdate=2018-03-14|archive-date=2018-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181108204550/http://mitsloan.mit.edu/newsroom/articles/rethinking-how-the-housing-crisis-happened/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 貿易失衡和債務泡沫 ===
