=== 货币政策 ===
另一種關於起因的敘事則關注公共貨幣政策（特別是在美國）和私人金融機構的實踐所扮演的角色的各個方面。在美國，抵押融資異常分散、不透明且具有競爭力，並且據信，貸方為了收入和市場份額的競爭導致承保標準下降和風險貸款。

儘管[[艾倫·格林斯潘|艾倫·格林斯潘]]（Alan Greenspan）擔任[[联邦储备系统|联邦储备系统]]主席的角色被廣泛討論，但爭議的焦點仍是將[[聯邦基金利率|聯邦基金利率]]降至1%以上長達一年多的時間，根據奧地利理論家的說法，這將大量「唾手可得的」基於信貸的資金注入了金融體系，造成了不可持續的繁榮，<ref>{{Cite news |last = Polleit |first = Thorsten |url = https://mises.org/story/2810 |title = Manipulating the Interest Rate: a Recipe for Disaster |publisher = Mises Institute |date = 2007-12-13 |accessdate = 2009-01-04 |archive-date = 2009-04-09 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090409061222/http://mises.org/story/2810 |dead-url = no }}</ref>還有一種觀點認為，格林斯潘在2002-2004年間採取的行動實際上是為了讓美國脫離[[互聯網泡沫|互聯網泡沫]]破裂導致的{{Tsl|en|Early 2000s recession|21世紀初經濟衰退}}——儘管這樣做無濟於事，只是推遲了危機。<ref>{{cite web |first = Ann |last = Pettifor |url = http://www.opendemocracy.net/article/america-s-financial-meltdown-lessons-and-prospects |title = America's financial meltdown: lessons and prospects |publisher = openDemocracy |date = 2008-09-16 |accessdate = 2009-01-04 |archive-date = 2008-12-16 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20081216072138/http://www.opendemocracy.net/article/america-s-financial-meltdown-lessons-and-prospects |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mises.org/story/1670|title=America's Unsustainable Boom|last=Karlsson|first=Stefan|date=2004-11-08|publisher=Mises Institute|accessdate=2009-01-04|archive-date=2009-05-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090525043851/http://mises.org/story/1670|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 私人債務高企 ===
